<!--
VOICING PLAN:
- M1 (D Bm): open ① D2-A2-D3-F#3, ⑥ Bm2-F#3-B3; RH 2-note light
- M2 (G): "43" ④¹ B4-E5 for RH, 4-note LH G2-D3-G3-B3
- M4 (A): ⑤² second inversion E4-A4-C#5 — sustained whole bar creates anticipation
- M6 (Em→A→G): ② Em full 4-note bass E2-B2-E3-G3
- M8 (A): ⑤ "33" A4-C#5-E5 — triumphant held dominant
- M10 (G→F#m7): ③7 F#m7 "333" A4-C#5-E5 — modal color in second half
- M12 (A7): ⑤7 complete dominant 7th A2-E3-G3-C#4 — rich leading to climax
- M13 (D d3/2 c/2): moving melody — inner voices "float" on two-chord pattern
- M15 (G D A): clean final cadence progression
- M16: ① "334" with D1 pedal — regal close

VOICE LEADING:
- M9→10: C#4 (RH) common between ① and ⑦°; stepwise descent in LH
- M11: ② Em "passing" measure — D4 in LH pedal connects ⑤→①
- M12: complete A7 creates strong dominant tension before final cadence
- M14: ②7→④→⑤→① four-chord final cadence pattern — all hands moving

TEXTURE ARC:
- M1-4: Moderate — 2-3 note RH, 3-4 LH
- M5-8: Builds — ③ F#m color (M5), ⑤² suspension (M4/M8)
- M9-12: Intense — ⑦° chromatic (M9/M3), ③7 color (M10), full ⑤7 (M12)
- M13-16: Triumphant conclusion — ①"334" close, D1 pedal
-->
